post_text:
This Post Contains Important Information About the Start of the School Year:

Due to a delay in the arrival of technology devices, we are postponing the start of the school year to ensure that families have equitable access to digital learning. Grades 1 through 7th grade and essential worker childcare will now start on Monday, September 14th. Students in Kindergarten and Prekindergarten will start on Thursday, September 17th. We will be providing more information on our website later today after 2 pm to explain this decision. We are excited about the strong online program we developed and we look forward to launching it with our scholars soon!

post_text: It's time for our last staff spotlight of the year! Today we're featuring Ms. Margaret Madigan, a kindergarten teacher at Prodeo's St. Paul campus. A fun fact about Ms. Madigan is that she was born in Guatemala. When she's not at work, she enjoys cooking, going outside, catching up with old friends, and Facetiming her family in Wisconsin and New York. When she was a child, her favorite book was Brown Bear, Brown Bear, What Do You See? Her favorite thing about Prodeo is "the warm and welcoming environment that each person feels as they walk into the building. The staff that I work with are always willing to support each other." Thanks, Ms. Madigan!

post_text:
We want to extend a special thank you to our families, scholars, and staff who have been part of this unprecedented 19-20 school year. While we look to finish the year strong, Prodeo Academy leaders and staff are engaged in planning for the 20-21 school year. We are following the latest developments and regulations regarding school openings in the Fall and looking forward to a successful academic year come September.

At this time, while we do not know the exact blend of on-site and remote learning that will have to take place next year, Prodeo Academy is committed to serving every child. We recognize that some of our students will require distance learning as an option until a vaccine is available. For that reason, Prodeo Academy is committed to providing remote learning options to qualifying students in accordance with MDE and state guidance, while also ensuring that scholars returning to classes on campus remain healthy and safe.

Please visit our website for updates throughout the summer about our distance learning and school reopening plans.

post_text:
Dear Prodeo Community,

The news in the past 24 hours has been overwhelmingly tragic. George Floyd’s killing is a reminder of our worst fears for our students, staff, and community. George Floyd mattered. This is incredibly painful. It continues to cause deep wounds that divide our community. The pain is public and real. All of us are hurting, and we also recognize that our pain can differ based on race, gender, lived experience and many additional factors. There is so much to be said, and we want to hold space for these conversations. Through the feelings of sadness, frustration, and fury, we must continue supporting each other, our scholars, our families, and the communities we serve. Though our work continues from a distance, we must remain close, so please reach out to any one of us as you need. We are here together, in pain and in solidarity, as we work toward a more just future for our society.

-Chancey, Rick, and the Prodeo team

Thank you Prodeo families for your participation in Distance Learning!

Before we depart for the summer, Prodeo Academy will be distributing end of year report cards and re-collecting all laptops, tablets, and books that were loaned out to families. Families must return any borrowed technology back to the school in good condition or may be liable for the cost of repair and replacement.

Families should return their borrowed devices and chargers to their campus (either MPLS or St. Paul) starting on Monday June 8th through Wednesday June 10th from 8 am to 4 pm. Upon the return of their scholar’s device, the family can pick up their report card.

If you think you’ll need home pickup of your borrowed device or have any questions, please call the school.

post_text: For today's staff spotlight, we're featuring Mr. Michael Kurhajetz, Prodeo's Vice President of Operations and Compliance. Mr. Kurhajetz once lived in Central America for six months, learning to scuba dive and backpacking around. When he's not working, he's playing outside with his kids! As a child, his favorite book was The Snarkout Boys and the Avocado of Death, by Daniel Pinkwater. His favorite thing about Prodeo is the passionate and dedicated staff! We'll leave you with some wise words from Mr. Kurhajetz himself: "One of my core beliefs is: "You CAN get there from here." The path may be long, difficult, and full of difficult trade-offs, but you CAN get there from here." Thanks for all you do!

post_text:
Hello Prodeo families! Under Governor Walz's new Executive Order to combat the COVID-19 pandemic, schools in Minnesota will offer Distance Learning for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Prodeo Academy will continue to offer classes online, while providing services such as meal distribution and childcare for emergency and medical workers at school sites. To prepare for the Extended Distance Learning Period, we are mandated to make Friday May 1st and Monday May 4th, planning days for our teachers. Any new distance learning work will be posted by Friday and families should use the weekend and Monday to catch up on any incomplete work from the past few weeks.

Work packets and materials for the Extended Distance Learning period for scholars in PreK, Kindergarten, 1st Grade, and 5th Grade must be picked up from the school starting on Monday May 4th from 8:00 am to 3:30 pm.

Please contact the school with any questions.

Attention Prodeo families! Minneapolis families may be eligible for housing assistance due to the COVID-19 crisis.

The city of Minneapolis emergency housing fund will be opening at 9 am on Wednesday, April 22nd for families struggling to pay for housing during the COVID-19 crisis. Applications can be submitted on the gap funding page. All Minneapolis families at or below 30% the area median income ($30,000) are eligible to apply for the $2 million emergency housing fund. We have heard that the city anticipates these funds will go fast so please apply as early in the process if you are eligible.

post_text: Happy Wednesday, Prodeo families! Today we're featuring Ms. Mary Barsness, the assistant principal in our Minneapolis Middle Academy. Ms. Barsness started a non profit called No Helmet No Ride to encourage people to wear helmets on bikes, blades and boards. It's now run by Regions Hospital. She says "I'm a nut about safety, just ask the kids!" When she's not at Prodeo, Ms. Barsness loves to cook, parent, plan her garden all winter and weed her garden all summer. She became a reader when a teacher read The Lion, the Witch, and the Wardrobe to her class. What she loves most about Prodeo is that "our students are the best, and I love that the people who work here use equal parts data and heart." Thanks, Ms. Barsness!

Hello Prodeo Academy families! In line with Governor Walz’s order from Wednesday, March 25th, all Minnesota schools will remain closed to students until at least May 4th, with students participating in distance learning until that time.

Prodeo’s teachers are working diligently to ensure that all families have at least one internet-connected device that students will be able to use each school day. Please contact the school or your student’s teacher right away to arrange a pick up.

Also, a quick reminder that Prodeo Academy will be on Spring Break next week -- March 30th through April 3rd -- so we won’t be providing childcare or food distribution. We’ll officially start the distance learning period on Monday, April 6th, and food distribution and childcare for eligible families will re-start that day as well. Thank you and please be safe and healthy during the shelter in place period! Keep up with updates on our website: prodeoacademy.org/apps/pages/COVID19

#stayhomeMN #Prodeoathome

post_text: While we may not be physically in our schools anymore, we can still celebrate our amazing staff! Mr. Alex McCoy is a first-grade teacher and grade team lead at our Minneapolis campus. He comes from a family of educators: his mom (college professor), aunt, cousin, and grandparents all are/were educators. His wife and her parents are educators as well! When he's not at work, Mr. McCoy enjoys hanging out with family and friends, cooking, watching movies, and listening to music. As a child, his favorite books were Ender's Game by Orson Scott Card and There Are No Children Here by Alex Kotlowitz. His favorite thing about Prodeo is the scholars and their families. A very exciting fun fact is that Mr. McCoy and his wife are expecting their first child this month! Thanks for all you do, Mr. McCoy.

post_text:
In order to be able to ensure all of our scholars have a device that will allow them to access schoolwork from home, we are asking that the community help support us in raising additional funds! We need to purchase additional tablets/Chromebooks in order to provide all of our scholars with high-quality educational access. We currently have 700 students across our network, and we would need an additional 350 devices to achieve 1:1 tech. Each device costs $290, so every dollar counts! Not only will this support help us in the short-term, but it will also help us to provide a long-term foundation of technology for all students for years to come. It has been our priority over the past several years to increase our capacity to achieve 1:1 tech, so let’s make something positive happen during this unprecedented moment. Please contribute whatever you can to help us reach our goal of 1:1 tech, in order to provide our scholars with continued education during this difficult time. Donate by visiting our website today!

https://www.prodeoacademy.org/apps/pages/donate

Prodeo families without internet access may be able to receive free internet through the next two months. Effective Monday, March 16, 2020, anyone who signs up for Internet Essentials will receive two free months of Internet service. We are also increasing the speed of the program to 25 Mbps downloads, and 3 Mbps uploads for all new and existing customers.

After your first two free months expire, you can either cancel the service (which you can do at any time) or keep it as a regular paying Internet Essentials customer. Please visit https://www.internetessentials.com/covid19 to apply.

Ms. Kim appreciates "the shared vision of the staff members to support the education AND social development of our children. Everyone really lives into the mission statement of Prodeo." Today's spotlight features Ms. Marian Pintar, a Second-grade Teacher at our St. Paul campus. A little-known fact about Ms. Pintar is that she's a blue belt in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu and has won gold in 5 tournaments! When she's not teaching, she's training at the gym or hiking outdoors. She also enjoys cooking, eating, and snuggling with her cat, Munchkin. Her favorite part about Prodeo? She says, "I am so, so grateful to be a part of a school that has such love and compassion for everyone in it. Students show each other such kindness, and staff are all so deeply committed to doing what is best for every child." Thanks, Ms. Pintar!

#ProdeoPRIDE #Prodeostaffspotlight

post_text:
Don't forget!

Back to School Day is tomorrow, Thursday, August 15th. This event is a perfect opportunity for you to meet your scholar’s teacher, buy uniforms, receive transportation times and equip your family for the upcoming school year. This week teachers have started reaching out to families to schedule a time slot for your scholar during the day. If you have not yet received a phone call please contact our front office at 763-205-9950 (Minneapolis) or 651-350-7655 (St. Paul).

Minneapolis Middle Academy families will not have specific appointments for Back to School Day, but should still attend to chat with Middle Academy leaders, get transportation information, see a video of our under-construction space, and hear about our Middle Academy schedule. Uniforms will be available for purchase from 3-6, but ordering online is always available. Our formal Middle Academy Information night will be September 11th at 6pm.

Prodeo St. Paul will have Uniform Day today, August 14th, from 3-6.

We can't wait to see you all!

post_text: AdoptAClassroom.org surprised Prodeo Minneapolis Kindergarten teacher Ms. Lindley for Teacher Appreciation Day! Congratulations, Ms. Lindley! We are grateful for your amazing work in your classroom. #ProdeoPRIDE #ProdeoMpls
shared_text:
AdoptAClassroom.org
May 7, 2019 at 9:01 PM ·

For #TeacherAppreciationDay, we surprised Prodeo Academy - Minneapolis kindergartner teacher, Emma, with $1,000 to purchase classroom supplies! Her students were SO excited to hear their classroom was getting a makeover with new materials.
